parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch can cause the motorcycle to lose power, making it difficult or impossible to accelerate, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear
difficulty shifting
especially from 1st to 2nd gear
and difficulty finding neutral.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden failure of the clutch can cause the motorcycle to lose speed or stall, leading to a loss of control, especially at high speeds, which can increase the risk of accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The motorcycle suddenly loses speed
the engine RPMs drop
the clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the motorcycle stalls or hesitates.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden loss of oil can cause the engine to seize, leading to costly repairs or even engine failure, which can leave the rider stranded or cause accidents.
symptoms: The oil light comes on
the engine dies
the motorcycle has no oil or low oil levels
the motorcycle is difficult to start or stalls frequently.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Inoperative turn signals can increase the risk of accidents, as other drivers may not be aware of the motorcycle's intentions, leading to potential collisions.
symptoms: The turn signal lights do not function
the turn signal lights are dim or flickering
the turn signal switch is faulty.
